Key trends shaping the global fiber cement market:



Shift Towards Environment-Friendly Building Materials: Due to rising environmental consciousness, demand is moving towards sustainable fiber cement products over asbestos or wood-based alternatives. This is a key trend.

Innovations in New Production Technologies: Manufacturers are adopting latest production technologies like Hatschek, extrusion and molding to enhance quality and efficiency. Additionally, R&D in self-cleaning fiber cement is rising.

Proliferation of Wood Grain Textured Fiber Cement: Manufacturers are innovating with wood grain textures and patterns in fiber cement cladding to make it more aesthetically appealing replacement for wood siding products.

Surging Adoption in External Wall Applications: Low maintenance and long service life is resulting in wider adoption of fiber cement boards, panels and sidings in external wall cladding and false ceiling applications.

Growing DIY Applications in Interior Home Improvement: Easier workability is facilitating increased uptake of fiber cement for do-it-yourself applications in interior ceilings, walls, floor underlayments etc.

Compliance with Green Building Standards: Fiber cement materials are increasingly being used in green buildings focused on sustainability to comply with LEED, BREEM, Greenstar and other regulations.

